A regular approach for playing `videos as a textures` in ARKit app, doesn&#39;t work with YouTube videos. But if you&#39;re interested in this approach I&#39;m writing it here (to find out how to feed a texture):

    func renderer(_ renderer: SCNSceneRenderer,
                 didAdd node: SCNNode,
                  for anchor: ARAnchor) {
     
        if let planeAnchor = anchor as? ARPlaneAnchor {

            let playerGeo = SCNPlane(width: CGFloat(planeAnchor.extent.x),
                                    height: CGFloat(planeAnchor.extent.z))
                 
